        <num>SRULE 13.3</num>
        <heading>Section </heading>
        <content>
          <p>Rule 13.3. Absences from committee meetings; removal
Each committee chairman shall notify the President of the unexcused absence of any member from three committee meetings during a session and shall notify the President of excessive absences in the interim. Any member who fails to attend three committee meetings during a session without being excused by the chairman may be removed as a member of the committee by the President. The chairman also is authorized to request the President to remove any member for excessive absences in the interim, and the President may remove such members.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=180413</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
